From: Daniel Pawlik <pawlik.dan@gmail.com>
Subject: cpufreq: airoha: fix dev_pm_domain_attach_list return value check

dev_pm_domain_attach_list() returns the number of attached domains on
success (a positive integer) or a negative error code on failure. The
driver checks "if (ret)" which incorrectly treats a successful attach
(returning 1) as an error.

This was a latent bug masked by the pmdomain driver never loading due
to a Kconfig dependency issue (fixed in patch 940). Once the pmdomain
driver probes, attach_list returns 1 and cpufreq probe bails out with
"error 1".

Change the check to "if (ret < 0)" to only treat negative values as
errors.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Pawlik <pawlik.dan@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/cpufreq/airoha-cpufreq.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/cpufreq/airoha-cpufreq.c
+++ b/drivers/cpufreq/airoha-cpufreq.c
@@ -64,7 +64,7 @@
 	/* Attach PM for OPP */
 	ret = dev_pm_domain_attach_list(cpu_dev, &attach_data,
 					&priv->pd_list);
-	if (ret)
+	if (ret < 0)
 		goto clear_opp_config;

 	cpufreq_dt = platform_device_register_simple("cpufreq-dt", -1, NULL, 0);
